    	<h2>General Information</h2>
    	<p>Whyteboard is programmed using the <a href="http://python.org" target="_blank">Python programming language</a>, and uses the <a href="http://wxpython.org" target="_blank">wxPython GUI framework</a>.</p>
    	
    	<p>You'll probably want a decent understanding of Python and wxPython in order to add features or fix bugs, as the program abstracts upon a lot of wxPython's classes. Read "<a href="http://wiki.wxpython.org/How%20to%20Learn%20wxPython" target="_blank">How to learn wxPython</a>" for more information.</p>
    	
    	<h2>Programming Whyteboard</h2>
    	<p>You'll want to read the <a href="http://bazaar.launchpad.net/~sproaty/whyteboard/development/view/head:/DEVELOPING.txt" target="_blank">DEVELOPING.txt</a> file in the program's source code. 
    	It contains general information regarding the class structure, coding style and gives an overview of the program.</p>
    	
    	<h3>Check out the source code</h3>
    	<p>You can use either <a href="http://bazaar.canonical.com" target="_blank">Bazaar</a> or <a href="http://git-scm.com" target="_blank">Git</a> -</p> 
    	<ul class="unstyled">
    		<li><code>bzr branch lp:whyteboard</code> or</li>
    		<li><code>git clone git://github.com/sproaty/whyteboard.git</code></li> 
    	</ul>
